quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  2,38,"We said, \"Go down, all of you, from here: then when guidance comes to you from Me, anyone who follows My guidance will have no fear, nor will they grieve"
  2,39,those who deny and reject Our signs shall be the inhabitants of the Fire; therein shall they abide forever
  2,40,"Children of Israel, remember the favours I have bestowed upon you, and fulfil the covenant that you made with Me. I shall fulfil the covenant I made with you. Fear Me alone"
  2,41,"And believe in the message I have sent down which fulfils that [predictions about the last prophet in their Scripture] which you already possess and do not be foremost among those who deny its truth. Do not sell My revelations for a paltry price; fear Me alone"
  2,42,"Do not mix truth with falsehood, or hide the truth when you know it"
  2,43,"Attend to your prayers, give the zakat [prescribed alms] and bow down with those who bow down"
  2,44,Do you admonish others to do good and forget this yourselves? Yet you read the Book. Will you not then understand
  2,45,"Seek help with patience and prayer; this is indeed an exacting discipline, but not to the humble"
  2,46,"who know for certain that they will meet their Lord, and that they will return to Him"
  2,47,"Children of Israel, remember My blessing which I have bestowed on you, and how I favoured you above all other people"
  2,48,"Guard yourselves against the Day on which no soul shall in the least avail another, when neither intercession nor ransom shall be accepted from it nor shall help be given to it"